ÚÄ--Operation
ÀÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ--ú ú   ú

   1.   Unzip this archive wherever you want.  TelePort can run from any
        directory on your drive.

   2.   Set TelePort up to run after a user logs on or when a user logs
        off.  It's at your descretion.
        Execute it as ...

       TelePort {Telegard's Data dir} {Portal's main dir} [Portal Task]

     Telegard's Data Dir
      - This is the complete path to Telegard's Data directory
        (i.e.  D:\Telegard\Data)

     Portal's Main Dir
      - This is the complete path to Portal of Power's main directory
        (i.e.  D:\Portal)

     Portal Task
      - This is an optional parameter.  If included, it is used to denote
        which Portal??.Dat file to write to, where ?? is the current task,
        in hex. The environment variable %PopTask% contains this information
        in a multiline environmeny.
        (i.e.  TelePort D:\Telegard\Data D:\Portal 2   - or -
               TelePort D:\Telegard\Data D:\Portal %PopTask%)
        If this parameter is excluded, TelePort will write to Portal.Dat.

